  "payload_text": "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n<!--\nDesign by Maya Horton and Martin Hardcastle. Modified extensively from --\n  --an original at https://templated.co.\n-->\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n<title>LOFAR surveys &mdash; welcome</title>\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:200,300,400,600,700,900|Quicksand:400,700|Questrial\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n<link href=\"/static/default.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" />\n<link href=\"/static/fonts.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" />\n<link href=\"/static/width.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" />\n<!--[if IE 6]><link href=\"default_ie6.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><![endif]-->\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"https://cdn.datatables.net/1.10.19/css/jquery.dataTables.css\">\n <script src=\"https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.min.js\"\n  integrity=\"sha256-FgpCb/KJQlLNfOu91ta32o/NMZxltwRo8QtmkMRdAu8=\"\n  crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> \n<script type=\"text/javascript\" charset=\"utf8\" src=\"https://cdn.datatables.net/1.10.19/js/jquery.dataTables.js\"></script>\n\n</head>\n<body>\n<!-- Note, the following section has been restructured -->\n<div class=\"bg-img\">\n  <div class=\"header_container\">\n          <div class=\"topnav\">\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"collaborators.html\">For Collaborators</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"releases.html\">Data Releases</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"publications.html\">Publications</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"astronomers.html\">For Astronomers</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"gallery_preview.html\">Image Gallery</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"citizen.html\">Citizen Science</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"surveys.html\">The Surveys</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n            <!-- <a href=\"index.html\">Welcome</a> -->\n            <!--  -->\n\t    \n\t    <a href=\"/login\">Log in</a>\n\t    \n\t    \t<div class=\"dropdown\">\n\t      \t\t<button class=\"dropbtn\">For astronomers</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<i class=\"fa fa-caret-down\"></i> \n\t      \t\t</button>\n\t      \t\t<div class=\"dropdown-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/publications.html\">Publications</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/releases.html\">Data releases</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/lotss-tier1.html\">LoTSS Tier 1</a>\n\t      \t\t</div>\n\t    \t</div> \n\t    \t<div class=\"dropdown\">\n\t      \t\t<button class=\"dropbtn\">News and media\n\t\t\t\t\t<i class=\"fa fa-caret-down\"></i>\n\t      \t\t</button>\n\t      \t\t<div class=\"dropdown-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/news.html\">News</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/gallery_preview.html\">Image gallery</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"/credits.html\">Credits</a>\n\t      \t\t</div>\n\t    \t</div> \n\t    \t<a href=\"/citizen.html\">Citizen Science</a>\n\t    \t<a href=\"/surveys.html\">The surveys</a>\n\t    \t<a href=\"/index.html\">Welcome</a>\n\n          </div>\n        </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"wrapper\">\n\t<div id=\"welcome\" class=\"container\">\n\n  \n    \n    \n<a href=\"gallery.html?file=static/gallery/B3_0157%2b406.png\"><img class=\"image-right\" src=\"static/gallery/B3_0157+406.png\" align=\"right\"></a>\n<div class=\"title\">\n\t  <h2>Welcome to the LOFAR Surveys website</h2>\n\t\t</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"page\" class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <p>Performing increasingly sensitive surveys is a fundamental\n    endeavour of astronomy. Over the past 60 years, the depth,\n    fidelity, and resolution of radio surveys has continuously\n    improved. However, new, upgraded and planned instruments are\n    capable of revolutionising this area of research.\n    The <a href=\"https://www.lofar.org/\">International Low-Frequency\n    Array (LOFAR)</a>, operated by\n    the <a href=\"https://lofar.eu/\">LOFAR ERIC</a>, is one such\n    instrument. LOFAR offers a transformational increase in radio\n    survey speed compared to existing radio telescopes. It also opens\n    up a poorly explored low-frequency region of the electromagnetic\n    spectrum. An important goal that has driven the development of\n    LOFAR since its inception is to conduct wide and deep surveys in\n    order to advance our understanding of the formation and evolution\n    of galaxies, clusters, and active galactic nuclei (AGN).</p>\n\n  <p>Explore this website to learn more about <a href=\"surveys.html\">the LOFAR surveys</a> and\n  their scientific results, including our <a href=\"releases.html\">data releases</a>, <a href=\"publications.html\">publications</a> and <a href=\"citizen.html\">citizen science programme</a>.</p>\n    <p>If you are looking for the surveys Wiki site (collaborators only) it is <a href=\"https://lofarwiki.strw.leidenuniv.nl\">here</a>.</p>\n    <p id=\"news\">NEWS: <a href=\"dr3.html\">LoTSS DR3 is released</a> (<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.15949\">Shimwell et al 2026</a>) (19/02/26)</p>\n<p id=\"news\">NEWS: <a href=\"https://ras.ac.uk/news-and-press/research-highlights/most-powerful-odd-radio-circle-date-discovered\">Most powerful 'odd radio circle' to date is discovered</a> (<a href=\"https://academic.oup.com/mnras/article/543/2/1048/8267915\">Hota et al 2025</a>) (02/10/25)\n    <p id=\"news\">NEWS: <a href=\"deepfields_dr2.html\">Deepest ever low-frequency radio image</a> is released (<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.04093\">Shimwell et al 2025</a>) (09/01/25)</p>\n<p id=\"news\">NEWS: <a href=\"https://www.caltech.edu/about/news/gargantuan-black-hole-jets-are-biggest-seen-yet\">Gargantuan Black Hole Jets Are Biggest Seen Yet</a> (18/09/24)\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n\t  \n</div>\n<div id=\"copyright\">\n<p>Site written in Python\n  using <a href=\"http://flask.pocoo.org/\">Flask</a>. Design modified\n  by <a href=\"https://mayahortonarts.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Maya\n    Horton</a> from <a href=\"http://templated.co\"\n\t\t       rel=\"nofollow\">TEMPLATED</a> under\n  a <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/uk/\"\n       rel=\"nofollow\">CC.BY 2.0</a> licence.</p>\n<p>For website issues please contact <a href=\"mailto:m.j.hardcastle@herts.ac.uk\">Martin Hardcastle</a></p>\n</div>\n<script>\n  $(document).ready( function () { \n  $('#table_id').DataTable({\n  \"pageLength\": 25});                                                 \n} );                                                                            \n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
